social_posts.post_text: What shaft are y’all using? From a clinic at the @worldgolfvillage this weekend. I used to think the faster the swing, the stiffer the flex. This isn’t necessarily true, and has more to do with how the player loads the shaft.

Want to drive it farther? You can improve your swing, improve your equipment, OR - add more horsepower 🐴 
  I teach you how to build a “bigger motor” safely in my course, “Strength and Power Training for Golfers” available now on my website, JustinJamesGolf.com 
➡️ go there now for a FREE mini course on loading powerfully in the backswing
#golf #golfswing #golflife #golfexcercise #golfcourse #golftips

🚨 If you don’t load the trail side properly, you’re robbing yourself of distance and accuracy! This is an excerpt from my free mini course, “Load to Launch” that will teach you what a loaded, balanced backswing should look like.
#golf #golftok #golftiktok #golfswing #golftips #golfchampion #golfer #golfexercise #golflife

Here’s a snippet from my “Load to Launch” course, available for free on my website, JustinJamesGolf.com. This is one of the best drills you can do to feel  the correct trail side loading pattern, and to develop more mobility. #golftiktok #golftok #golf #golftips #golfer #golfcourse

💪🏼 The @mobility_wall is one of my favorite and most used tools for increasing and maintaining mobility. If you have tightness in the traps and shoulders - this is an absolute must have. It’s hard to make a free flowing, powerful swing when your restricted and tied up

🚨 Here’s a completely free mini course for you guys on loading more powerfully and efficiently in your backswing. This WILL increase your club head speed and tighten dispersion if you are currently out of balance and not loading correctly. Looking forward to helping y’all hit it longer in 2023!

@golf_for_c.o.p.s hosts one of the best events in the country. A ton of fun, and raising 💰 for a great cause. This was my winning shot from 2020. Looking forward to participating again soon
#golf #golfer #golfswing
🎄 Thanks to @powerplateusa for an early Christmas present. Excited to share some great training protocols and exercises on this bad boy!

🚨 You have yards / distance in the tank you aren’t using, and it doesn’t involve weightlifting or speed training. 
 The Steep to Shallow course is for people who know they have more speed in the tank with the driver. 
 - so many people I teach want more club head speed, but aren’t using the speed they already have to optimize distance. This course will show you how to optimize and bomb the driver.
 - link in bio

Atlantic City was my favorite stop on Tour - this is from 2018, where I took 3rd. When I started to struggle with my swing a bit, my footwork got sloppy - you can see me “artificially” keeping the trail heel down through impact instead of letting the hips fly. Despite struggling to find my swing in this stretch, I still hit the ball nicely for the majority of 2018, making every final 8 and winning in Tennessee. 
#golf #golfer #golfswing #goldchampion #golftips #golflife

Here’s a go to drill for beginners! 
  Many golfers I work with are surprised that the majority of force needs to come from the LEAD - not trail side. If you want to start hitting the ball better this is a great drill!

2022 World Championship. Launch angles continue to rise with advancements in tech (lower spin drivers and golf balls). If you want an IMMEDIATE distance hack - try launching the ball higher. Check out my FREE Load to Launch course to learn how to load powerfully, and increase attack angle. @prolongdrive #golf #golflife #golfer #goldchampion #golfswing

Playing, testing and working on some stuff in the garage with @swingbalanceai and @onform_app 
  Technology is pretty cool 😎
🔥 A few movements I’ve been using on the @powerplateusa Move. This was a part of a push workout. The Move gives a great stimulus that really 💡‘s you up.

🔥 To accelerate the club head forward, push away from the target and golf ball from the ball of your lead foot. This will also help eliminate early extension. This is a huge un-tapped power source for most golfers. ⛳️ 
 
➡️ need help? Check out my online courses - link in bio. 
➡️ OR - schedule an online lesson with me

Here’s some “golf course” work. My LD & golf swing have some similarities, but also some major differences. It’s very difficult in my experience to blend and differentiate the two, but I feel I’m getting better at it 💪🏼
 One thing that’s absolutely essential to hitting the driver well - load powerfully behind the golf ball. If you’ve got questions on what that means - I’ve got a free course for you to check out - link in bio.

🚀 This was the most satisfying shot I’ve ever hit - exact shot shape, trajectory, etc. Final yardage was 469. Denver was an incredible venue - it’s a bummer this venue no longer exists. Looking forward to creating some more memories in 2023 👊 

 ➡️ check out the trail leg & lead foot

  LOAD TO LAUNCH - Link in bio!
⭐️ It’s been a blast hitting balls under the lights @ UNF. I think we need some more night golf in this world 🌎

➡️ Amateurs use metal, pros use wood - just like baseball. Good idea? Not realistic - but if I had a Time Machine, I think it would be interesting 🤔 
  There’s no better feeling than munching a wood driver (with a modern ball 😂)
💪🏼 If your a high speed player - ADDING Spin might reeaaallllly help on the golf course. Have you tired any of these? Which have worked?
🤖 One of my favorite pieces of training equipment - who knows what it is? And who’s used it? 🔥

🚨 Don’t make the mistake of coming up and out of posture in the takeaway. This is an absolute KILLER that separates good and poor players. Consistent spine angles in your swing will help with consistency and POWER as you’ll hit the center of the face more, and maintain better balance!

➡️ Don’t forget the importance of lateral force in the swing. You’ve got to load, then push LATERALLY into your lead side to properly transition and slot the club. 
 ➡️ Clink the link in bio for more
Learned this from @malaskagolf - a great tip that will help you next time you play. Give this a shot with warming up and drill work. Let me know what you think
➡️ If your not flaring your back foot already - give it a try. For most, it really helps their backswing load. For more info - check out my courses (link in bio)
🚨 Swing the driver (slightly) differently than your irons for better results. Click the link in my bio for my new course, Driver 101, where we go over some of the intricacies of hitting the driver.

From quarter finals of 2016 @worldlongdrive championship. Swing was in a great spot at the time - I like how the club head stays “in front, and the club head tips above the plane coming into impact. If you want to hit the ball straight, we want to hands to work away from the golf ball, not toward the golf ball.

💪🏼 Fun Kettlebell exercise. Not for beginners, but a great variation that will reinforce change of pressure and the sequencing that we need in our golf swing. Kettlebells can be great training aids when used correctly. This doesn’t mirror the swing exactly - in fitness, we look for general similarities from different movement patterns that add athleticism, speed and power.
@powerplateusa makes the simple exercises you are already doing better. If you’ve never used one before, it’s worth checking out. 🔥

Width in the takeaway can help increase club head speed. This is one factor or “hack” of many that can get you more yards, right now. My new Driver 101 course goes over many of these “Driver Hacks.” Link in bio

@rotexmotion work for the day. If you aren’t Rotexing … your missing out

Justin is super expanding his ribcage by pushing one shoulder blade down and pulling the other one up as far as possible (against the tension of the resistance band). 

He allows his body and feet to turn on the ROTEXMotion Floor Models as he opens his ribcage.

Then, he holds that position of his upper body as he counter-rotates his feet and ankles against maximum resistance. 

This creates an isometric tension throughout his entire body, stressing all the muscles, tendons, and joints.

The OUTCOME is a superior activation to help get the body ready for extreme performance.
